First note that a negative divided by a negative is positive. Then rewrite the division as multiplication by the reciprocal:

\[
- \tfrac{7}{27} \div \bigl(-\tfrac{35}{36}\bigr)
= \bigl(-\tfrac{7}{27}\bigr)\;\times\;\bigl(-\tfrac{36}{35}\bigr)
= \tfrac{7}{27}\times\tfrac{36}{35}.
\]

Now simplify:
\[
\tfrac{7}{27}\times\tfrac{36}{35}
=\tfrac{7\cdot36}{27\cdot35}
=\tfrac{7\cdot(36/9)}{(27/9)\cdot35}
=\tfrac{7\cdot4}{3\cdot35}
=\tfrac{28}{105}
=\tfrac{4}{15}.
\]

Answer: \(\displaystyle \tfrac{4}{15}.\)
